originalText.text: I have never dealt with a worse financial company.  I sent in my 529 transfer for deposit at the beginning of November.  After at least six phone calls, the money is still not credited.  They have asked me the same questions over and over, and then say the deposit will be expedited and then, I check a week later.  Nothing.  A minimum of a 20 minute hold every time.  This last time, I was berated for not having my confirmation number from the last phone call, as if they can't look on my account.  And it's impossible to do even routine transactions online. They don't have the technology.  You know how they do the 529 rollover?  Fax. Wow.

originalText.text: The online website is extremely poorly done and is not user friendly at all. I would not recommend this if you have any other options. I'm not sure if I could have started a 529 plan for my grandchildren any other way but I would surely have done a lot more research had I experienced this website beforehand.

originalText.text: Do not consider moving your 401k plan to Vestwell.  Worst customer service and nobody responds to emails.  It has taken over 6 months for them to convert our plan from another provider and it still isn't finished.  Wish we never even considered this firm!

originalText.text:
My job unfortunately switched payroll company’s and we ended up with vestwell for our 401(k) plan. This is by far the worst and least technically advanced company I’ve had to use for a 401(k). I haven’t even started the process of rolling over my account but I already can tell it’s going to be frustrating and probably take longer than it needs to be. I wish I had just rolled over my old account and stopped taking the benefit than to work with vestwell.

I also find it high key shady that they have so many reviews talking about how they handle peoples money yet haven’t made any changes to better their “business” it’s giving scam.
